gomodel:SYNGO_5282  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1b: ARMS (gene KIDINS220) is detected in synaptic biochemical fractions from hippocampal neurons, co-migrating with Trk receptors and GluA1 (GRIA1) in various subfractions from P2.\n\nFigure 1c: immunogold EM showed of hippocampal CA1 showed ARMS localized to endomembranes in the dendritic shaft and spine. No presynaptic localization was observed.\n\nFigure 4: immunofluorescence imaging of 15DIV hippocampal neurons showed intracellular GluA1 co-localized with ARMS whereas surface GluA1 did not.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Electron microscopy - Adult male mice or Sprague-Dawley rats were anesthetized \"\n\nantibody:\n\"rabbit polyclonal (Kong et al., 2001) and mouse monoclonal ARMS antibodies (gift of G. Schiavo)\" PMID: 11150334\n\nFigure 1 of this PMID that authors refer to for the ARMS antibody shows the protein sequence and mention this is GenBank accession BAA86564, confirming this is human gene KIDINS220" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-09" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5282" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .
